WEBVTT

00:07.000 --> 00:09.667
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

00:55.767 --> 00:57.467
Hiya.
[ Clears throat ] Uh...

00:57.467 --> 00:59.700
I was -- I was told
I could borrow money here.

01:01.533 --> 01:03.067
Depends. Told by who?

01:03.067 --> 01:05.333
Uh, Rory, at the pub.

01:05.333 --> 01:07.067
He's -- He's my uncle.

01:10.067 --> 01:12.433
-You're Rory's nephew?
-Mm.

01:29.067 --> 01:30.667
You got collateral?

01:32.067 --> 01:34.467
-Yeah.
-[ Laughs ]

01:35.567 --> 01:36.900
What, you a time traveler?

01:37.733 --> 01:40.400
Did you just pop in
from the late '90s?

01:42.067 --> 01:43.767
That's worth feck all, mate.

01:46.067 --> 01:48.067
This is what phones
look like now.

01:50.733 --> 01:52.700
This is all I have.

01:53.567 --> 01:58.067
Since you're related to Rory,
I'll trust you, just this once.

02:00.800 --> 02:02.767
I'm not a time traveler.

02:03.533 --> 02:05.433
RINGO:
Whatever you say, mate.

02:09.800 --> 02:11.533
Hey, Rory
doesn't have siblings.

02:11.533 --> 02:13.133
-I'm a nihilist.
-[ Screams ]

02:13.133 --> 02:16.067
[ Theme music plays ]

02:45.233 --> 02:47.667
[ Toilet flushes ]

02:47.667 --> 02:50.500
Oh. [ Yawns ]

02:53.867 --> 02:55.600
I thought it was just one drink.

02:55.600 --> 03:00.300
Mm, yeah, well, we had one,
and then we had a few more.

03:02.067 --> 03:03.667
Any coffee?

03:03.667 --> 03:07.333
Mm.
Kitchen, black.

03:07.333 --> 03:09.067
No sugar for me.

03:10.333 --> 03:11.767
Okay.

03:12.733 --> 03:14.233
[ Harry sighs ]

03:15.600 --> 03:16.867
[ Door closes ]

03:23.233 --> 03:25.067
[ Humming ]

03:25.067 --> 03:26.467
[ Water running ]

03:28.067 --> 03:29.667
[ Knock on door ]

03:29.667 --> 03:31.367
-FERGUS: Harry!
-[ Doorbell rings ]

03:31.367 --> 03:33.633
-Harry, are you in there?
-[ Knock on door ]

03:34.667 --> 03:36.767
Harry!
Open up, it's Fergus!

03:36.767 --> 03:38.767
-[ Knock on door ]
-I need your help!

03:38.767 --> 03:41.267
[ Knocking continues ]

03:41.267 --> 03:42.633
[ Doorbell rings ]

03:42.633 --> 03:44.233
Harry!
Are you in there?!

03:44.233 --> 03:46.067
[ Knock on door ]

03:46.067 --> 03:47.167
It's Fergus!
Open up!

03:47.167 --> 03:50.500
[ Doorbell rings,
knock on door ]

03:52.400 --> 03:54.067
[ Harry sighs ]

03:54.067 --> 03:55.833
You'll never guess
what happened.

04:01.067 --> 04:03.067
This isn't a good time actually.

04:03.067 --> 04:04.567
It's Happy.

04:04.567 --> 04:06.800
He's heard about what you
and I've been doing.

04:06.800 --> 04:09.067
One of his loan sharks
was murdered last night.

04:09.067 --> 04:10.267
So?
Call the guards.

04:10.267 --> 04:11.633
He doesn't trust the guards!

04:11.633 --> 04:14.067
I don't care!
I'm not gonna help him.

04:14.067 --> 04:16.800
He threatened to break
your little sister's arm,

04:16.800 --> 04:18.067
or have you forgotten that?

04:18.067 --> 04:19.633
Course I haven't
bloody well forgotten.

04:19.633 --> 04:21.167
Look, he's promised to rip up

04:21.167 --> 04:24.067
Malky's debt
if we find out what happened.

04:24.067 --> 04:25.867
-[ Sighs ]
-Harry, I'm gonna do this

04:25.867 --> 04:27.533
with or without you.

04:27.533 --> 04:29.300
I'd prefer it to be with.

04:31.267 --> 04:33.267
[ Sighs ]

04:38.467 --> 04:40.633
[ Whispering ] You can let
yourself out when we're gone.

04:46.600 --> 04:48.467
Wait, why are there
two mugs out?

04:50.067 --> 04:51.167
Oh, God.

04:52.567 --> 04:54.500
[ Gulls crying ]

05:03.067 --> 05:05.067
Listen, whatever happens,

05:05.067 --> 05:07.867
don't mention him
threatening Liberty, okay?

05:14.767 --> 05:16.667
HARRY: Hm.

05:16.667 --> 05:19.067
So you're her, eh?

05:19.067 --> 05:21.367
No, she couldn't make it,
so I came instead.

05:22.633 --> 05:24.333
You what?

05:24.333 --> 05:27.167
Yeah, yeah.
Happy, this is Harry.

05:27.167 --> 05:28.833
She was just joking.

05:30.867 --> 05:33.067
Oh.

05:33.067 --> 05:35.433
-You think is funny, do you?
-No, I don't.

05:35.433 --> 05:39.800
Much like threatening
to break little girls' arms.

05:42.267 --> 05:44.567
Business is business,

05:44.567 --> 05:48.467
and you'd want to keep yours
out of mine, love.

05:48.467 --> 05:52.433
You invited me into
your horrid little business.

05:52.433 --> 05:55.067
Well, I can go, and
you can find out what happened

05:55.067 --> 05:56.700
to your employee on your own
if you prefer.

05:57.733 --> 05:59.467
He wasn't my employee.

06:02.167 --> 06:03.567
He's my son.

06:04.667 --> 06:06.567
No way.

06:06.567 --> 06:08.167
Ringo was your son?

06:08.167 --> 06:09.900
He was.

06:10.733 --> 06:13.167
Except he didn't know.

06:13.167 --> 06:15.733
We never told him.

06:15.733 --> 06:18.433
Never told anyone.

06:18.433 --> 06:20.433
Only me and his mammy knew.

06:24.533 --> 06:26.133
You hungry?

06:26.133 --> 06:27.333
Help yourself.

06:27.333 --> 06:28.867
This is my restaurant.

06:28.867 --> 06:30.633
You're my guests.

06:30.633 --> 06:31.867
You're Mr. Pang?

06:31.867 --> 06:33.133
No.

06:33.133 --> 06:34.667
He's Pang.

06:34.667 --> 06:37.200
Borrowed some money,
couldn't pay it back.

06:37.200 --> 06:39.567
Now I own a restaurant.

06:39.567 --> 06:41.767
He loves me, the little fucker.

06:41.767 --> 06:44.200
Says [Imitating Pang mockingly]
"Ah, Mr. Happy.

06:44.200 --> 06:46.867
You make my life
so much easier now."

06:46.867 --> 06:48.800
I don't speak like that.

06:48.800 --> 06:52.500
[ Laughs ]
Have you no dishes to wash?

06:55.633 --> 06:58.400
Ringo was a good boy.

06:58.400 --> 07:01.067
A bit too nice
to be a moneylender.

07:01.067 --> 07:03.767
Lapped up all the sob stories.

07:05.767 --> 07:08.167
Someone split his head in two
with an ax.

07:13.067 --> 07:15.833
We do this, I have conditions.

07:15.833 --> 07:20.100
One, I'm not serving anyone up
to be murdered back.

07:20.833 --> 07:23.433
That's not happening,
and there's no discussion.

07:23.433 --> 07:28.133
Number two, when we're done,
you rip up Malky's debt,

07:28.133 --> 07:30.567
and you never go anywhere
near Fergus' family again.

07:30.567 --> 07:33.167
[ Laughs ]

07:33.167 --> 07:35.667
The mouth on this one.

07:35.667 --> 07:38.133
I like you, Your Highness.

07:38.133 --> 07:39.733
You've got balls.

07:39.733 --> 07:41.667
I do.

07:41.667 --> 07:45.067
Great big hairy ones.

07:45.067 --> 07:47.300
So, let's go, shall we?

07:48.067 --> 07:49.067
Where?

07:50.233 --> 07:52.100
Scene of the crime.

08:15.833 --> 08:17.067
Oh.

08:18.667 --> 08:20.467
Don't touch anything.

08:28.067 --> 08:30.467
The writing's part
of a longer quote.

08:31.367 --> 08:35.267
"The darker the night,
the brighter the stars,

08:35.267 --> 08:38.133
the deeper the grief,
the closer is God."

08:38.133 --> 08:40.067
God's nowhere near this place.

08:40.067 --> 08:43.200
It was written by a poet,
Apollon Maykov.

08:43.200 --> 08:46.467
He was a friend
of Fyodor Dostoevsky.

08:46.467 --> 08:47.767
Heard of him?

08:48.600 --> 08:50.767
Did he do the "Mr. Men" books?

08:51.867 --> 08:53.467
"The Brothers Karamazov"?

08:54.667 --> 08:56.667
"Crime and Punishment"?

08:56.667 --> 08:57.700
"The Idiot"?

08:59.333 --> 09:01.067
The quote is interesting

09:01.067 --> 09:04.367
because it's often attributed
to Dostoevsky.

09:04.367 --> 09:08.800
Common misconception that
it's in "Crime and Punishment."

09:08.800 --> 09:09.867
It's not.

09:19.533 --> 09:21.533
[ Switch clicks ]

09:21.533 --> 09:23.633
"Crime and Punishment's"
interesting.

09:23.633 --> 09:27.067
I must remember to put it
on my reading list.

09:27.067 --> 09:30.567
Raskolnikov, the main character,
kills a moneylender...

09:30.567 --> 09:32.067
albeit a woman in the book.

09:32.067 --> 09:34.067
What's that got to do
with anything?

09:34.067 --> 09:36.200
Ringo wasn't a woman
or a Russky.

09:36.200 --> 09:39.067
He was a moneylender,
and he was killed with an ax,

09:39.067 --> 09:41.267
which is what Raskolnikov uses.

09:41.267 --> 09:43.767
Wait, wait.
So what's it about?

09:43.767 --> 09:47.067
Raskolnikov thinks
he's superior,

09:47.067 --> 09:48.833
intellectually
and in every other way.

09:48.833 --> 09:51.400
He thinks he can get away
with murder.

09:51.400 --> 09:54.200
He kills the moneylender because
he considers her a crook,

09:54.200 --> 09:57.067
and then he accidentally
kills her half-sister,

09:57.067 --> 09:58.767
who's an innocent.

09:58.767 --> 10:00.633
After that,
he's racked with guilt,

10:00.633 --> 10:02.167
and it leads to his undoing.

10:02.167 --> 10:04.867
Ringo has a brother, right?

10:04.867 --> 10:06.233
Toby?

10:06.233 --> 10:08.333
Nothing to do with me, that one.

10:08.333 --> 10:10.533
He's a mentally challenged
young man.

10:10.533 --> 10:12.900
Yeah, but he's also
a half-brother.

10:15.867 --> 10:17.100
We have to find Toby!

10:21.633 --> 10:24.400
HAPPY THE SHARK: Derek,
it's Happy. Listen, mate.

10:24.400 --> 10:26.467
Derek, shut up.

10:26.467 --> 10:30.067
Derek, stop fecking crying
and put Sheila on the phone.

10:30.067 --> 10:31.367
Now!

10:31.367 --> 10:33.600
[ Keypad clicking,
cellphone chimes ]

10:37.067 --> 10:38.200
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:38.200 --> 10:40.033
[ Cellphone chimes ]

10:47.767 --> 10:50.400
Sheila? Where's Toby?

10:50.400 --> 10:53.000
We think whoever hurt Ringo
might go after Toby, too.

10:53.000 --> 10:55.267
Is he there?

10:55.267 --> 10:57.500
God give me strength!

10:59.367 --> 11:01.633
Sheila, just tell me
where he is!

11:03.867 --> 11:05.367
He's with the school.

11:05.367 --> 11:07.067
They haven't told him
about Ringo yet.

11:07.067 --> 11:08.733
He's on a school trip,
and she doesn't know where.

11:08.733 --> 11:11.633
Have her call the school,
find out.

11:11.633 --> 11:13.733
Sheila, listen to me.
This is important.

11:13.733 --> 11:15.400
Call the school.

11:15.400 --> 11:18.467
Find out exactly where he is
and then call me back.

11:18.467 --> 11:19.567
Have you got that?

11:20.233 --> 11:21.500
She's doing it.
Come on.

11:24.067 --> 11:26.100
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

11:45.767 --> 11:47.300
BILLY: [ Whistles ]

12:13.067 --> 12:14.800
TOBY:
How do you know me brother?

12:14.800 --> 12:19.267
Oh, we met recently
and really hit it off.

12:19.267 --> 12:21.067
He said you liked games.

12:21.067 --> 12:24.233
I'm really good
at "Gran Turismo."

12:24.233 --> 12:27.567
He lets me play it on his PS4.

12:29.467 --> 12:31.600
I'm not supposed
to go off alone.

12:31.600 --> 12:33.467
Ah, Toby, you're not alone.

12:33.467 --> 12:34.633
You're with me.

12:45.667 --> 12:48.633
Split up.
We can cover more ground.

13:16.233 --> 13:18.400
[ Panting ]

13:39.067 --> 13:41.367
-[ Gasps ]
-TOBY: Hello.

13:41.367 --> 13:44.067
Is it you I have to send
a message to?

13:44.067 --> 13:45.367
My arms hurt.

13:48.267 --> 13:50.400
Are you alright?

13:50.400 --> 13:52.067
Did he harm you?

13:52.067 --> 13:54.067
TOBY: He was nice.

13:54.067 --> 13:56.067
He was my friend.

13:56.067 --> 13:58.600
His name was really hard to say.

13:58.600 --> 14:00.200
Raskolnikov.

14:00.200 --> 14:02.067
Yeah, that's it.
Do you know him?

14:02.067 --> 14:03.667
Where did he leave the message?

14:06.067 --> 14:08.433
It tickled as he wrote it.

14:09.600 --> 14:11.533
So you were wrong.

14:11.533 --> 14:13.400
He's not copying
"Crime and Punishment."

14:13.400 --> 14:16.067
I never said he was.

14:16.067 --> 14:18.767
He has an agenda,
but he's not done yet.

14:35.233 --> 14:37.100
Usual, please, June.

14:39.333 --> 14:41.667
You'll never guess in a million
years what happened to me.

14:41.667 --> 14:43.367
You bumped into your ex, Petra.

14:43.367 --> 14:44.867
How the bloody hell
did you guess that?

14:44.867 --> 14:46.433
Well, your watch is missing.

14:46.433 --> 14:49.200
You keep your wallet
in your back pocket,

14:49.200 --> 14:51.433
and usually you're just tilting
a little bit.

14:51.433 --> 14:53.067
You're sitting up straight

14:53.067 --> 14:55.433
right now, so I'm guessing
that it's not there,

14:55.433 --> 14:57.433
and you've probably lost
your phone.

14:57.433 --> 15:00.333
Oh, great.

15:00.333 --> 15:01.833
Still, that was

15:01.833 --> 15:04.367
some pretty impressive
Sherlock shit right there.

15:04.367 --> 15:09.667
And I saw you getting
into her car at Lidl earlier.

15:09.667 --> 15:11.567
She always robs you.

15:11.567 --> 15:12.767
I don't know
why you keep putting

15:12.767 --> 15:14.067
yourself through all this.

15:14.800 --> 15:16.900
[ Sighs ]

15:19.067 --> 15:22.400
June, this one's on me.

15:22.400 --> 15:24.067
Bumped into Petra.

15:24.067 --> 15:25.533
JUNE: Oh, Glenn.

15:25.533 --> 15:28.067
Whenever will you learn?

15:28.067 --> 15:30.167
When his dick drops off,
like other men.

15:30.167 --> 15:32.067
[ Both laugh ]

15:32.067 --> 15:34.400
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

15:43.833 --> 15:46.267
Did either of you see
anyone here at my table?

15:46.267 --> 15:48.433
-Mnh-mnh.
-Apart from you?

15:48.433 --> 15:50.833
[ Sighs ]
Yes, Glenn, apart from me.

15:50.833 --> 15:53.100
No.

16:11.467 --> 16:13.767
BILLY: "My dearest Harry,

16:13.767 --> 16:15.867
I'm sure you can appreciate
my delight

16:15.867 --> 16:18.233
when I discovered who you are.

16:18.233 --> 16:21.433
It's kismet, don't you think?

16:21.433 --> 16:24.367
We're two sides
of the same coin, you and me.

16:24.367 --> 16:29.067
You use literature to solve
crimes, and I use it to murder.

16:29.067 --> 16:31.567
How perfect we are
for one another.

16:31.567 --> 16:34.567
Allow me to introduce myself.

16:34.567 --> 16:39.167
I am
Rodion Romanovitch Raskolnikov.

16:39.167 --> 16:41.233
I thought that we could
communicate through letters

16:41.233 --> 16:43.567
like in the book.
That's why I picked it.

16:43.567 --> 16:46.767
You could be Helene,
and I could be Frank.

16:46.767 --> 16:51.067
But when I thought it through,
it was impractical.

16:52.133 --> 16:54.667
So I thought of another way.

16:54.667 --> 16:59.433
Yours affectionately, R.R.R."

17:04.600 --> 17:06.400
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:12.067 --> 17:14.867
[ Cellphone rings ]

17:17.733 --> 17:19.500
[ Ringing continues ]

17:22.233 --> 17:23.267
BILLY: Hello, Harry.

17:25.400 --> 17:27.467
Call me Raskolnikov.

17:27.467 --> 17:29.067
No.

17:29.067 --> 17:31.067
You know my name.

17:31.067 --> 17:32.567
I need to know yours.

17:32.567 --> 17:35.433
-Rodion Romano--
-[ Cellphone beeps ]

17:36.833 --> 17:38.400
[ Sighs ]

17:38.400 --> 17:40.267
[ Cellphone rings ]

17:40.267 --> 17:43.200
-Don't do that ag--
-[ Cellphone beeps ]

17:46.567 --> 17:47.733
[ Keypad clicks ]

17:47.733 --> 17:50.333
[ Cellphone rings ]

17:50.333 --> 17:52.167
I'm warning you.

17:52.167 --> 17:54.067
-Don't make me angry.
-[ Cellphone beeps ]

17:55.067 --> 17:56.067
[ Clears throat ]

17:56.067 --> 17:57.867
[ Keypad clicks, line ringing ]

17:57.867 --> 17:59.067
Fine.

17:59.067 --> 18:01.067
It's Billy, it's Billy.

18:01.067 --> 18:03.067
Great.

18:03.667 --> 18:07.667
So what do you want to talk
to me about...Billy?

18:07.667 --> 18:12.067
Dostoyevsky's version of me
is all wrong.

18:12.067 --> 18:13.467
Weak.

18:13.467 --> 18:15.367
Consumed by guilt.

18:15.367 --> 18:19.667
I could've killed Toby,
but I didn't,

18:19.667 --> 18:23.367
because I was in control
the whole time.

18:23.367 --> 18:26.767
Did you ever actually read
"Crime and Punishment"?

18:26.767 --> 18:29.067
Of course I have.

18:29.067 --> 18:30.467
Time and time again.

18:30.467 --> 18:32.267
Well, it sounds like
you don't understand it.

18:32.267 --> 18:34.533
Oh, but I did.

18:34.533 --> 18:39.233
Oh, I did, Harry,
and it was a revelation.

18:39.233 --> 18:43.167
I could hear Dostoyevsky
speaking to me with every word.

18:43.167 --> 18:46.733
"You are Raskolnikov,"
he was saying.

18:46.733 --> 18:50.633
"The true Raskolnikov,
not this imposter on the page."

18:51.433 --> 18:56.533
And then I was in a pub,
and I overhead two men talking.

18:56.533 --> 18:58.167
One of them needed cash.

18:58.167 --> 19:02.067
His friend told him of
a moneylender who lived nearby.

19:03.233 --> 19:05.067
"Go see Ringo."

19:07.133 --> 19:10.067
I had the book in my hand,
Harry.

19:10.633 --> 19:12.367
I mean, it was a sign.

19:12.367 --> 19:14.767
A sign that you're a psychopath.

19:14.767 --> 19:17.500
You can't know me, Harry.

19:18.867 --> 19:21.267
I am the oceans.

19:21.267 --> 19:23.067
I'm a blade of grass.

19:23.067 --> 19:25.333
I'm a feather.
I'm the air.

19:25.333 --> 19:26.833
You're a fucking nutcase.

19:26.833 --> 19:29.333
Now, I thought you'd understand.

19:29.333 --> 19:31.767
Well, I do understand.

19:31.767 --> 19:35.233
We are two sides
of the same coin, remember?

19:35.233 --> 19:37.600
You want...

19:37.600 --> 19:38.867
No.

19:38.867 --> 19:41.433
No, you need me to stop you.

19:41.433 --> 19:43.200
You can't stop me.

19:43.200 --> 19:45.700
I've only just started this.

19:46.867 --> 19:48.433
And the moneylender
deserved to die,

19:48.433 --> 19:50.800
but what if I kill someone
who doesn't deserve it?

19:50.800 --> 19:53.333
You don't need to do this.

19:53.333 --> 19:56.100
To test myself, I do.

19:56.867 --> 20:00.033
I mean, how will I ever know
if I'm truly superior?

20:00.733 --> 20:02.800
You already have someone
in mind, don't you?

20:02.800 --> 20:05.033
Maybe.

20:05.567 --> 20:08.400
Someone who's just too perfect.

20:10.067 --> 20:12.667
And maybe if you're smarter
than me, you'll get there first,

20:12.667 --> 20:14.800
but hurry, Harry...

20:16.200 --> 20:19.500
...because he dies at 11:45.

20:28.333 --> 20:30.267
Can you narrow it down at all?

20:30.267 --> 20:31.867
I mean, is it an old book or...

20:31.867 --> 20:33.733
Oh, I don't know!

20:33.733 --> 20:36.067
Someone who dies clutching
a vital clue.

20:36.067 --> 20:39.467
It could be
a thousand different books.

20:39.467 --> 20:41.600
But I thought I had it.

20:41.600 --> 20:43.633
Just for a moment
when he said...

20:43.633 --> 20:45.800
Oh!

20:46.433 --> 20:50.000
So, how's Lola?

20:50.000 --> 20:52.067
Should I be disturbed
that we're trying to stop a man

20:52.067 --> 20:54.667
from being murdered and you're
thinking about my granddaughter?

20:54.667 --> 20:56.833
-Well, no, I mean...
-She's fine!

20:59.633 --> 21:01.733
She asked about you, too.

21:01.733 --> 21:03.800
Oh, did she, now?

21:03.800 --> 21:07.467
Well, is she calling 'round
any time soon or...

21:08.733 --> 21:10.267
[ Clears throat ]

21:11.767 --> 21:13.533
I'm gonna have to tell Charlie.

21:13.533 --> 21:14.867
Oh, you can't do that.

21:14.867 --> 21:17.667
Happy doesn't want
the guards involved.

21:17.667 --> 21:20.067
This is someone's life.

21:20.067 --> 21:23.067
How would you feel
if an innocent man died?

21:23.067 --> 21:25.067
Yeah, alright, but...
but what if Charlie

21:25.067 --> 21:26.667
doesn't listen to you,
as per usual?

21:26.667 --> 21:29.433
Well, there is someone else
I could talk to, but...

21:29.433 --> 21:31.200
[Sighs]
but we still have to find out

21:31.200 --> 21:32.467
who the victim's going to be.

21:32.467 --> 21:34.433
Well, we've got time, though,
right?

21:34.433 --> 21:37.233
I mean, it was gone a quarter
to 12:00 this morning

21:37.233 --> 21:39.733
when he called,
so we've got at least...

21:39.733 --> 21:42.067
That's it!
That's what I thought!

21:42.067 --> 21:44.433
It's not the vital clue!
It's time!

21:44.433 --> 21:46.133
Oh, Fergus, you're a genius!

21:46.133 --> 21:48.800
-Uh, what's happening now?
-Billy.

21:48.800 --> 21:53.067
Billy said 11:45,
not a quarter to 12:00.

21:53.067 --> 21:55.600
Yeah, but that's the same time,
so what difference does it make?

21:55.600 --> 21:57.800
Sherlock Holmes.
Ha ha ha!

21:57.800 --> 22:00.767
Oh, here. "Adventure
of the Reigate Squire."

22:04.267 --> 22:06.167
Oh, yeah.

22:06.167 --> 22:10.267
Dead man's found clutching a
torn piece of a note that reads,

22:10.267 --> 22:13.100
"At quarter to 12:00,
learn what may be."

22:14.467 --> 22:18.200
But his victim will be
called William Kirwan.

22:18.867 --> 22:22.600
We have to find him
before Billy kills him.

22:25.133 --> 22:27.633
[ Ringtone plays ]

22:30.633 --> 22:32.767
Can I call you back at --

22:33.433 --> 22:35.133
Of course there is.

22:35.133 --> 22:37.100
Who's going to be murdered now?

22:41.467 --> 22:44.167
[ Siren wailing,
police radio chatter ]

22:50.467 --> 22:52.067
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

23:24.667 --> 23:26.067
[ Mosky meows ]

23:26.800 --> 23:28.867
You don't look very lost to me.

23:45.433 --> 23:47.333
A.C. Mitchell-Tiernan.

23:47.333 --> 23:49.233
We did meet briefly, Mrs. Wild,

23:49.233 --> 23:51.667
at Charlie's little do
a few weeks ago.

23:51.667 --> 23:55.133
You may not recall, you were
rather excitable at the time.

23:55.133 --> 23:57.133
Of course now we know why.

23:57.133 --> 24:00.233
Yes, we do.
I bet you remember, of course.

24:00.233 --> 24:03.767
And it's Professor Wild,
not "Mrs."

24:03.767 --> 24:05.167
Never been a Mrs.

24:05.167 --> 24:08.067
And here we are in the same boat
once more.

24:08.067 --> 24:10.467
One would hope a woman
of your years would know better.

24:10.467 --> 24:12.333
Passes the time while I wait

24:12.333 --> 24:14.400
-for the bingo to open.
-[ Laughs ]

24:17.167 --> 24:19.200
A man is dead, Mrs. Wild.

24:19.200 --> 24:21.067
Levity's hardly appropriate.

24:21.067 --> 24:24.133
Gallows humor,
Mrs. Maxwell-Tanqueray.

24:24.133 --> 24:26.333
Mitchell-Tiernan, A.C.

24:26.333 --> 24:28.067
Oh, is that something to do
with air-conditioning?

24:28.067 --> 24:29.567
Assistant commissioner.

24:29.567 --> 24:31.600
Assistant?

24:31.600 --> 24:34.233
Any chance of a coffee?
Black, no sugar.

24:35.800 --> 24:37.067
What...

24:39.533 --> 24:41.767
Jesus, Harry, it's like
you've got bloody Tourette's.

24:41.767 --> 24:43.800
Life's too short to deal
with people like her.

24:43.800 --> 24:47.067
Go home. We have the phone
if he calls. We'll deal with it.

24:47.067 --> 24:49.600
I'm sure he'd much rather
talk to you than me.

24:55.433 --> 24:57.700
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

25:00.833 --> 25:03.433
[ Keys jingling ]

25:03.433 --> 25:04.600
[ Lock disengages ]

25:09.367 --> 25:10.733
-Hello, Harry.
-Aah!

25:10.733 --> 25:13.600
BILLY: Don't turn around,
don't turn around.

25:14.200 --> 25:15.667
I'm not gonna hurt you.

25:20.400 --> 25:23.800
I just didn't want to talk
with other people listening in.

25:25.067 --> 25:26.900
You lied.

25:27.533 --> 25:30.067
William Kirwan was already dead
at 11:45.

25:30.067 --> 25:32.433
BILLY: No.
You're reading too much into it.

25:33.167 --> 25:36.067
It was about the name.

25:36.067 --> 25:37.767
The name was enough.

25:39.833 --> 25:41.300
Want to know how I did it?

25:42.433 --> 25:44.767
I already know how you did it.

25:45.367 --> 25:46.500
The cat.

25:50.067 --> 25:52.533
Took him a couple of days ago.

25:53.533 --> 25:56.067
God, he was frantic
to get it back.

25:56.667 --> 25:59.233
He had 200 flyers
up around the place.

26:01.200 --> 26:02.800
And he was so grateful

26:02.800 --> 26:05.367
when I showed up
with that flea-bitten thing.

26:07.533 --> 26:10.167
Didn't think twice about
turning his back on me then.

26:13.433 --> 26:16.400
Writing the quote in cat food.

26:17.067 --> 26:18.800
It's a nice touch.

26:21.267 --> 26:23.233
Thank you.

26:23.233 --> 26:26.133
See, I like cat food.

26:26.133 --> 26:30.833
It has an excellent
adhesive quality.

26:30.833 --> 26:32.833
Covered a teacher's car in it
once before.

26:32.833 --> 26:35.567
She didn't much appreciate that.

26:37.733 --> 26:39.433
So what are you going to do now?

26:43.067 --> 26:44.633
Are you feeling guilty?

26:50.733 --> 26:52.700
Not a bit.

26:54.067 --> 26:56.167
As for what's next,
I don't know.

26:56.167 --> 26:59.200
I haven't really decided that.

27:01.067 --> 27:02.867
But when I do...

27:07.400 --> 27:09.167
...you'll be
the first one I call.

27:19.633 --> 27:21.467
Oh, God.

27:21.467 --> 27:24.067
Oh! [ Sighs ]

27:24.067 --> 27:25.800
How are you so bleedin' calm
about it?

27:25.800 --> 27:27.067
He was in your car!

27:27.067 --> 27:28.233
I know!

27:28.233 --> 27:30.067
I was in there, too.

27:30.067 --> 27:32.067
He doesn't want to hurt me.

27:32.067 --> 27:33.133
You can't know that!

27:33.133 --> 27:34.533
You couldn't possibly know that!

27:34.533 --> 27:37.800
He needs to prove
that he's smarter than me.

27:37.800 --> 27:39.533
He can't do that if I'm dead.

27:39.533 --> 27:40.867
He's insane, Harry.

27:40.867 --> 27:43.367
Insane means unpredictable.

27:44.567 --> 27:45.833
[ Scoffs ]

27:50.533 --> 27:53.400
What's this Book of Dicks, then?

27:53.400 --> 27:56.833
It's an online forum
for teachers and lecturers.

27:56.833 --> 28:00.367
We share horror stories
about pupils.

28:00.367 --> 28:02.433
Most inventive acts
of disobedience,

28:02.433 --> 28:04.400
pranks, that sort of thing.

28:04.400 --> 28:06.500
Like covering a car in cat food?

28:07.433 --> 28:10.067
It happened to a teacher
at St. Iona's Private School

28:10.067 --> 28:11.633
six years ago.

28:11.633 --> 28:14.067
I spoke to the teacher
this morning.

28:14.067 --> 28:17.567
She knew exactly who did it,
but she couldn't prove it.

28:17.567 --> 28:20.067
The pupil's name was Billy Lund.

28:20.067 --> 28:22.400
This is his family home.

28:22.400 --> 28:24.400
Yeah, not the sort of place
you'd expect a nutter

28:24.400 --> 28:27.167
-like him to grow up.
-Hmm.

28:28.433 --> 28:31.200
Gosh, what can I say
about myself?

28:31.200 --> 28:34.133
I love to find the essence
of truth in the mundane.

28:34.133 --> 28:38.833
The way a leaf tilts,
shadow on brick.

28:38.833 --> 28:41.067
Beautiful.

28:41.067 --> 28:42.333
So tell me about your gallery.

28:42.333 --> 28:44.600
Oh, no, it's not my gallery.

28:44.600 --> 28:47.433
The owner wishes to remain
incognito for now.

28:47.433 --> 28:49.267
But he's interested in my work?

28:49.267 --> 28:51.067
It's early days yet,

28:51.067 --> 28:53.267
and we still have a lot
of people to see, but...

28:53.267 --> 28:56.367
I must say, your work
really does stand out.

28:56.367 --> 28:58.067
I'd love to see some more.

29:00.067 --> 29:03.167
Jacques, make sure
that shipment goes out today.

29:03.167 --> 29:07.067
Patrick, it's alright
if he makes a few calls here?

29:07.067 --> 29:08.800
Absolutely.
Make yourself at home.

29:08.800 --> 29:11.067
-Come.
-Okay.

29:17.333 --> 29:19.167
These are striking.

29:19.167 --> 29:20.633
Tell me about them.

29:20.633 --> 29:23.633
Ah, well, that was ambitious.

29:23.633 --> 29:26.067
It was going
to be called "25" --

29:26.067 --> 29:28.300
one photo every day
for 25 years.

29:29.767 --> 29:31.533
HARRY:
They're all the same person?

29:31.533 --> 29:34.067
PATRICK:
Yeah, my son Bill.

29:34.067 --> 29:38.600
25 years.
That's 9,000-plus photos.

29:38.600 --> 29:40.633
That's a lot to ask
of a young man.

29:40.633 --> 29:41.633
PATRICK: Clearly.

29:41.633 --> 29:44.333
He left a thousand photos early.

29:44.333 --> 29:48.133
"25" became "22 and 114 Days."

29:48.133 --> 29:50.333
Not so snappy.

29:50.333 --> 29:52.067
Such a selfish little...

29:52.067 --> 29:54.067
[ Sighs ]

29:54.067 --> 29:57.633
We don't always know
where we went wrong, do we?

30:04.000 --> 30:05.033
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

30:17.200 --> 30:19.500
Who the bloody hell are you?

30:20.433 --> 30:22.600
Why are you in my kitchen?

30:22.600 --> 30:25.400
I'm Fer-- Jacques.
I'm -- I'm...

30:25.400 --> 30:26.833
I'm Jacques.

30:26.833 --> 30:29.600
My boss is talking with Mr. Lund
right now.

30:29.600 --> 30:31.367
Is -- Is he your dad?

30:31.367 --> 30:33.133
He's my fiancé.

30:33.133 --> 30:35.767
Oh.
Oh, right. Sorry.

30:35.767 --> 30:38.233
What are you doing
with his laptop?

30:38.233 --> 30:41.367
That?
Um, yeah, I'm...

30:41.367 --> 30:44.800
I'm trying to keep my job,
you know?

30:44.800 --> 30:47.333
My boss, she's a total dragon,

30:47.333 --> 30:51.733
and, uh, well, I forgot to put
something on my phone,

30:51.733 --> 30:54.067
so she'll bloody kill me,
you know?

30:54.067 --> 30:57.533
-Who's your boss?
-She works with this gallery.

30:57.533 --> 31:00.067
She's talking with your da--
uh...

31:00.067 --> 31:04.067
man about an exhibition
in New York.

31:04.633 --> 31:07.067
Ha! I'll be on show.

31:07.067 --> 31:08.667
'Cause that's me!

31:10.400 --> 31:13.067
Bloody hell!

31:13.067 --> 31:14.767
Yeah.

31:15.667 --> 31:17.300
Oh, here.

31:21.067 --> 31:23.067
Thanks.
That's amazing.

31:23.067 --> 31:25.200
You're --
I mean, thank you.

31:25.200 --> 31:26.467
That's very nice of you.

31:33.067 --> 31:34.067
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

31:34.067 --> 31:36.267
PATRICK:
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

31:36.267 --> 31:38.800
I don't regret
a second I spent on it.

31:38.800 --> 31:41.833
Still, I'll always see it
as unfinished.

31:41.833 --> 31:43.367
-HARRY: Mm.
-Hello, darling.

31:43.367 --> 31:45.267
SIOBHAN: Ah.

31:45.267 --> 31:46.800
Hi.

31:47.533 --> 31:50.067
-Come here. Mm.
-PATRICK: Mwah.

31:50.067 --> 31:52.167
Miriam,
this is my fiancée, Siobhan.

31:52.167 --> 31:54.200
Siobhan, Miriam represents --

31:54.200 --> 31:56.233
Yeah, I met Jacques,
and he told me.

31:56.233 --> 31:58.133
So what are you two
talking about?

31:58.133 --> 31:59.533
"25," of course.

31:59.533 --> 32:01.833
Oh. [ Sighs ]
Such a shame.

32:01.833 --> 32:03.767
Paddy put so much time
and effort into it,

32:03.767 --> 32:05.600
but Billy
was always a bit selfish.

32:05.600 --> 32:06.833
You know Billy?

32:06.833 --> 32:08.767
Oh, God, yes.
I knew Billy first.

32:08.767 --> 32:10.567
We went to school together.

32:10.567 --> 32:12.667
Childhood sweethearts.

32:12.667 --> 32:16.067
We were engaged for a bit,
a couple of years.

32:16.067 --> 32:17.433
Four.

32:17.433 --> 32:19.067
-Mm.
-Mm-hmm.

32:19.067 --> 32:21.067
And now you're marrying his dad.

32:21.067 --> 32:22.833
[ Laughs ] I know.

32:22.833 --> 32:24.633
Pads and I laugh about it
all the time,

32:24.633 --> 32:26.733
but we were just kids then,

32:26.733 --> 32:30.167
like, barely in our 20s,
and I was a late developer.

32:31.733 --> 32:34.767
These just practically popped up
overnight, didn't they, Pads?

32:34.767 --> 32:37.833
-Oh, yes.
-Mm-hmm. Mm.

32:37.833 --> 32:38.867
-Mm.
-Mm.

32:39.067 --> 32:40.467
-Mm.
-Mm.

32:47.567 --> 32:50.067
-[ Clears throat ]
-[ Clears throat ]

32:50.067 --> 32:51.600
That was uncomfortable.

32:51.600 --> 32:53.067
I mean, I don't know
what kind of thing

32:53.067 --> 32:54.800
turns a person into a psycho,

32:54.800 --> 32:57.767
but your girlfriend
doing the dirt with your da?

32:57.767 --> 32:59.267
Well, it can't help.

32:59.267 --> 33:03.633
And he photographed him
every day for 22 years.

33:04.600 --> 33:06.633
You said he was a big fella.

33:06.633 --> 33:10.100
He looks like a strong wind
could snap him in two.

33:11.867 --> 33:14.200
He reinvented himself.

33:14.200 --> 33:16.467
He grew up dominated
by his father.

33:16.467 --> 33:20.167
The one good thing in his life,
his girlfriend, blossoms,

33:20.167 --> 33:24.333
and Patrick Lund notices her,

33:24.333 --> 33:26.067
takes that from him, too.

33:26.600 --> 33:28.133
Billy doesn't want to be
weak anymore,

33:28.133 --> 33:30.333
so he hits the gym,
makes himself

33:30.333 --> 33:33.200
physically powerful,
but that's not enough either.

33:33.200 --> 33:35.867
He still feels inadequate.

33:37.233 --> 33:40.333
Then along comes Dostoyevsky,

33:40.333 --> 33:44.067
and in Billy's warped mind
somewhere, he...

33:44.067 --> 33:47.267
he thinks the answer
to all his problems is to kill,

33:47.267 --> 33:48.800
like Raskolnikov.

33:50.733 --> 33:52.167
Killing makes him feel
in control

33:52.167 --> 33:54.067
for the first time in his life.

33:56.233 --> 33:58.800
And I don't think
he's gonna stop.

34:09.067 --> 34:12.067
The suspect's name
is Billy Lund.

34:12.067 --> 34:13.867
OFFICER: Approaching
suspect's front door.

34:22.367 --> 34:24.367
Breaching now.
Go, go, go!

34:30.067 --> 34:31.633
-OFFICER #2: Moving.
-OFFICER #1: Go, go, go, go, go!

34:31.633 --> 34:33.600
Move, move, move!
Upstairs!

34:37.567 --> 34:40.067
Clear.
There's no one here.

34:40.067 --> 34:42.100
[ Sighs ] Bollocks!

34:45.767 --> 34:46.767
[ Line ringing ]

34:46.767 --> 34:49.067
[ Cellphone rings ]

34:55.333 --> 34:57.067
BILLY:
It was mentioning my old teacher

34:57.067 --> 34:59.167
and the cat food, wasn't it?

34:59.167 --> 35:01.167
Cat food? What the hell
are you talking about?

35:01.167 --> 35:02.467
No, you've messed
with my family.

35:02.467 --> 35:04.767
Now I'm gonna mess with yours.

35:04.767 --> 35:07.300
Got a little granddaughter,
right?

35:10.067 --> 35:11.567
[ Keypad clicking ]

35:14.600 --> 35:16.200
Charlie...

35:16.200 --> 35:17.833
Charlie, pick up.

35:24.833 --> 35:27.067
Your da had to nip out.

35:27.067 --> 35:29.067
I said I'd mind your sister
till you got back.

35:32.067 --> 35:34.233
Come on, Libby.
Bath time.

35:34.233 --> 35:36.567
We didn't even finish our game.

35:36.567 --> 35:38.600
Oh, I think you had me beaten.

35:38.600 --> 35:41.800
You'd better do what your
big brother tells you, huh?

35:41.800 --> 35:43.600
[ Liberty sighs ]

35:43.600 --> 35:45.233
FERGUS: Come on, stinker.

35:45.233 --> 35:46.667
Wait for me upstairs, alright?

35:52.133 --> 35:54.067
You and Her Majesty
getting anywhere?

35:54.833 --> 35:57.067
Yeah. We're close.

35:58.667 --> 36:01.400
Have you got a name for me yet?

36:01.400 --> 36:03.500
Don't lie to me, boy.

36:04.133 --> 36:05.900
I'll know if you're lying.

36:08.067 --> 36:11.100
Not yet, but soon.

36:12.433 --> 36:14.700
It's not an exact science,
you know.

36:25.667 --> 36:30.500
Tell Her Highness from me --
I'm not a patient man.

36:42.767 --> 36:44.300
[ Sighs ]

36:56.367 --> 36:58.367
In you go, love.

36:59.233 --> 37:00.867
I'll be right behind you.
You'll be fine.

37:00.867 --> 37:02.467
Okay.

37:08.600 --> 37:10.433
[ Sighs ]

37:16.433 --> 37:17.900
[ Locks disengage,
car alarm chirps ]

37:23.067 --> 37:24.867
[ Keys jingling ]

37:26.233 --> 37:28.400
[ Grunting ]

37:46.433 --> 37:49.067
[ Ringtone plays ]

37:52.733 --> 37:55.233
Orla?
Are you guys okay?

37:55.233 --> 37:56.800
ORLA:
Lola and I are at the station.

37:56.800 --> 37:58.833
We're fine, but something's
happened to Charlie.

37:58.833 --> 38:00.333
He's disappeared!

38:00.333 --> 38:03.133
-What?!
-ORLA: He was supposed to be

38:03.133 --> 38:05.367
-right behind us!
-[ Cellphone rings ]

38:05.367 --> 38:07.367
No one knows where he is, Har--

38:11.133 --> 38:12.733
Billy?

38:12.733 --> 38:14.067
What have you done?

38:14.067 --> 38:16.200
Just what I said I'd do.

38:16.200 --> 38:19.067
If you hurt Charlie, I...

38:19.067 --> 38:22.467
What? You'll what?

38:22.467 --> 38:24.167
Hunt me down?

38:26.200 --> 38:28.700
You think you're better than me.

38:29.333 --> 38:30.633
Superior.

38:30.633 --> 38:33.067
Superior?
No, no, I'm not superior.

38:33.067 --> 38:35.467
Well, there's only one way
to know for sure.

38:37.067 --> 38:39.467
I'm gonna kill your son, Harry.

38:39.467 --> 38:41.233
Don't you dare.

38:41.233 --> 38:45.200
BILLY:
I'm gonna kill your son at 5:00.

38:45.200 --> 38:48.067
That gives you exactly one hour
and four minutes,

38:48.067 --> 38:52.067
and I've given you
everything you need to find me.

38:54.367 --> 38:57.433
Let's see who's really superior.

38:58.633 --> 39:01.067
[ Breathing heavily ]

39:03.133 --> 39:05.533
[ Knock on door ]

39:05.533 --> 39:07.100
FERGUS: Harry!

39:08.600 --> 39:11.067
Are you in there?
It's Fergus.

39:11.067 --> 39:14.067
Happy's fumin' you brought
the guards into this.

39:14.067 --> 39:15.667
-He said he's gonna --
-He's got Charlie.

39:15.667 --> 39:17.533
-What? Who, Happy?
-No, Billy!

39:17.533 --> 39:19.267
Billy's got Charlie!

39:19.267 --> 39:21.400
He told me I had until 5:00
to find him.

39:21.400 --> 39:23.767
He said that he'd given me
everything that I need.

39:23.767 --> 39:26.067
-What has he given me?
-The phone, right?

39:26.067 --> 39:28.167
No. I looked at it.
There's nothing there.

39:28.167 --> 39:30.367
Uh, how about the book?
"84 Whatsit."

39:30.367 --> 39:32.733
I -- No, it's that...

39:32.733 --> 39:34.400
that quote.

39:34.400 --> 39:37.200
"The darker the night,
the brighter the stars."

39:37.200 --> 39:38.533
The poster, right?

39:38.533 --> 39:40.667
There was a poster
on Ringo's wall.

39:40.667 --> 39:43.067
Oh, it was by your man.
What's his name?

39:43.067 --> 39:44.567
-Van Gogh.
-HARRY: I saw that.

39:44.567 --> 39:46.067
I'd forgotten about it,

39:46.067 --> 39:48.267
but it was called
"The Starry Night."

39:48.267 --> 39:49.800
How do you know it?

39:49.800 --> 39:52.067
Well, it was on the wall
of the art room at school.

39:52.067 --> 39:54.400
I used to stare at the thing
twice a week, right,

39:54.400 --> 39:57.800
but the darker the night --
a night sky.

39:57.800 --> 40:00.533
Oh, my God! Yes, yes!
You clever boy.

40:00.533 --> 40:02.667
"The brighter the stars."
There were stars and moons

40:02.667 --> 40:05.000
all over the ruins
when we found Toby!

40:05.000 --> 40:06.433
Yeah, exactly, right?

40:06.433 --> 40:08.600
"And the deeper the grief."
William Kirwan.

40:08.600 --> 40:12.267
He'd lost his cat. That's
sort of grieving, isn't it?

40:12.267 --> 40:15.200
Tenuous, but very Billy.

40:16.000 --> 40:17.667
"The closer is God."

40:19.167 --> 40:20.533
Charlie's in a church!

40:20.533 --> 40:22.033
A church?
In Dublin?

40:22.033 --> 40:24.267
Yeah, that really
narrows it down. Which one?

40:24.267 --> 40:26.067
[ Keypad clicking ]

40:26.067 --> 40:28.033
No, hang on a second.
There is something on here.

40:28.033 --> 40:31.367
"Cool Atim." Right, he's got
the high score on "Snake."

40:31.367 --> 40:34.067
In fact, it's the only score.

40:34.767 --> 40:36.767
I know where he is.

40:36.767 --> 40:38.367
Cool Atim.

40:38.367 --> 40:43.133
Church of
our Lady and the Irish Martyrs.

40:43.133 --> 40:44.567
It's up by the People's Park.

40:48.333 --> 40:50.433
Ray!
Call me when you get this!

40:50.433 --> 40:53.033
I think I know where Charlie is.

40:55.800 --> 40:57.733
Happy, they're on the move.

40:57.733 --> 40:59.200
Call you when I know
where they're heading.

40:59.200 --> 41:00.367
[ Engine starts ]

41:00.367 --> 41:02.067
[ Tires screeching ]

41:28.067 --> 41:29.567
[ Whispering ]
No one seems to be here.

41:29.567 --> 41:31.167
Why are you whispering?

41:31.167 --> 41:33.067
I don't know.
It's a church, isn't it?

41:33.067 --> 41:35.467
HARRY: [ Sighs ]

41:35.467 --> 41:36.833
Shit!

41:36.833 --> 41:38.167
I jumped to conclusions.

41:38.167 --> 41:39.633
Maybe it was something
in the book.

41:39.633 --> 41:42.267
Something I didn't see.
And I left it behind.

41:42.267 --> 41:44.633
[ Sighs ]
We only have 10 minutes left.

41:44.633 --> 41:46.867
Fergus, oh, God,
what am I going to do?

41:46.867 --> 41:48.400
Charlie could...

41:52.200 --> 41:53.667
"Crime and Punishment."

41:53.667 --> 41:55.300
He's here.

41:59.200 --> 42:01.067
Okay, he's marked
a passage here.

42:01.067 --> 42:03.567
Something to do with Napoleon.

42:03.567 --> 42:07.367
Blah blah blah. "Master"...

42:07.367 --> 42:09.800
[ Speaking gibberish ]
"Massacre in Paris.

42:09.800 --> 42:12.667
Forgets an army in Egypt.

42:13.433 --> 42:16.067
Jest at Vilna.
Altars set up to him

42:16.067 --> 42:17.267
after his death all of --"

42:17.267 --> 42:18.600
Napoleon.

42:18.600 --> 42:20.233
Yeah, he was a general,
a French general.

42:20.233 --> 42:21.800
No, no, no. Harry.

42:23.600 --> 42:25.200
Oh.

42:37.067 --> 42:39.067
[ Gasps ]

42:39.067 --> 42:41.133
Time to call in the cavalry.

42:41.133 --> 42:44.167
Shit! No signal.

42:44.167 --> 42:45.433
Stay here.

42:45.433 --> 42:47.567
He doesn't know
that you're with me.

42:48.800 --> 42:51.500
If things go wrong, get help.

43:04.067 --> 43:05.700
Charlie, can you hear me?

43:09.333 --> 43:11.067
Ow! [ Gasps ]

43:11.067 --> 43:13.100
Shh! Where is he?

43:14.333 --> 43:16.133
I don't know.
I don't know.

43:16.133 --> 43:18.067
I don't remember.
I, uh...

43:18.067 --> 43:19.333
Lola! Orla!

43:19.333 --> 43:21.667
They're fine.
They're at the station.

43:23.533 --> 43:25.133
I came through the tunnel,
but I can't get you out.

43:25.133 --> 43:26.367
It's too narrow.

43:26.367 --> 43:28.733
BILLY:
You made it just in time, Harry.

43:28.733 --> 43:30.633
[ Clock chiming ]

43:34.267 --> 43:36.067
Did I make it too easy?

43:36.067 --> 43:38.200
No.

43:38.200 --> 43:39.800
No, you made your point.

43:41.800 --> 43:44.200
But the guards are coming.

43:44.200 --> 43:46.867
BILLY: Fergus!

43:47.600 --> 43:49.600
I know you're there.

43:50.267 --> 43:52.467
Wherever Harry goes,
you're never really far behind,

43:52.467 --> 43:54.900
so just come out now!

43:56.267 --> 43:58.433
He's not here.

43:58.433 --> 44:00.667
I didn't have time to get him.
You only gave me an hour.

44:00.667 --> 44:02.200
Well, let's hope he is in there

44:02.200 --> 44:03.767
because I'm gonna count to three

44:03.767 --> 44:06.367
and then I'm gonna cut
your son's hand off.

44:06.367 --> 44:08.600
-One!
-Billy.

44:08.600 --> 44:10.733
-He's not here.
-Two!

44:10.733 --> 44:12.167
You're gonna have
to kill me first!

44:12.167 --> 44:13.833
No, I won't!

44:13.833 --> 44:15.500
I won't!

44:17.200 --> 44:19.600
I am so much stronger than you.

44:22.600 --> 44:25.400
I'll just push you
out of the way.

44:25.400 --> 44:27.067
-Aah!
-Get off her!

44:27.067 --> 44:29.067
-Three!
-Alright, alright! Stop, okay?

44:29.067 --> 44:31.467
I'm here.
Just put her down, please!

44:31.467 --> 44:32.800
-Stay there!
-Okay, okay!

44:32.800 --> 44:34.600
Stay back!

44:35.833 --> 44:38.233
It's over now, Billy.

44:39.067 --> 44:42.300
I got here before 5:00.
I win.

44:48.600 --> 44:50.833
I think I made it too easy.

44:50.833 --> 44:54.600
Make it harder next time,
but tonight, I win.

44:54.600 --> 44:58.533
Next time,
it'll be so much harder.

44:58.533 --> 45:01.067
You'll see.

45:01.067 --> 45:04.067
You'll be even more motivated
to stop me

45:04.067 --> 45:06.067
because I'll have
killed your son.

45:06.067 --> 45:07.433
No, no.

45:07.433 --> 45:09.567
No, if you do that,
then it's over.

45:09.567 --> 45:10.767
I won't play your game anymore.

45:10.767 --> 45:12.367
[ Sarcastically ]
Yeah, right!

45:12.367 --> 45:14.200
You'll just walk away!

45:14.200 --> 45:15.767
You!

45:15.767 --> 45:18.233
Leave it to the others
to stop me?!

45:21.267 --> 45:23.067
-Aah!
-Harry!

45:23.067 --> 45:24.267
Put that down, boy.

45:28.233 --> 45:31.067
This is the first time I've
ever been pleased to see you.

45:33.200 --> 45:34.633
How did you know
we were down here?

45:34.633 --> 45:37.067
I didn't.
Thought you were upstairs.

45:37.067 --> 45:39.433
We were going to sneak up
on you.

45:39.433 --> 45:42.067
Not many people know
about this tunnel.

45:42.067 --> 45:44.200
Me, I was an altar boy here.

45:44.200 --> 45:46.500
Shut up!
Just shut up!

45:47.800 --> 45:49.433
This was a private gathering.

45:49.433 --> 45:51.233
Neither of you were invited.

45:53.233 --> 45:54.800
I'll just have to kill
you both now.

45:54.800 --> 45:57.233
There's only one person
dying here today, son.

45:57.233 --> 45:59.367
We're not talking about killing.
No one's gonna be killed here.

45:59.367 --> 46:01.200
That's right because
you're all under arrest.

46:01.200 --> 46:03.333
-Lay down your weapons.
-[ Laughs ]

46:03.333 --> 46:04.867
HARRY: You're handcuffed
to a bloody wheelchair.

46:04.867 --> 46:06.633
No one's going to listen to you.

46:06.633 --> 46:08.767
Bullets are faster than axes,

46:08.767 --> 46:11.067
and you're going to pay
for Ringo.

46:11.067 --> 46:13.367
Think about it, Happy.

46:13.367 --> 46:16.067
If you kill him, you're killing
him in front of a guard.

46:16.067 --> 46:19.200
Be smart, do the right thing,

46:19.200 --> 46:21.200
and a guard
will be in your debt.

46:21.200 --> 46:22.767
No, I bloody won't.

46:22.767 --> 46:25.533
HARRY: He's saving your life.
Yes, he will.

46:25.533 --> 46:30.067
He can't get you off a crime,
but he will owe you a favor.

46:30.667 --> 46:32.267
I really want to kill him,
though.

46:32.267 --> 46:33.400
FERGUS: But Ringo...

46:34.767 --> 46:37.167
...he wouldn't want you to,
right?

46:37.167 --> 46:39.067
He's right, Happy.

46:39.067 --> 46:41.067
Ringo hated violence.

46:41.067 --> 46:44.567
If it'd make you feel better,
you could shoot him in the leg.

46:46.133 --> 46:47.533
What?

46:47.533 --> 46:48.600
He's not gonna...

46:49.067 --> 46:50.400
Oh! Oh!

46:50.467 --> 46:53.433
Oh! Oh! Oh!

46:53.433 --> 46:55.633
You were right.

46:55.633 --> 46:57.467
That did make me feel better.

46:57.467 --> 46:58.567
-BILLY: Oh!
-Fergus!

46:58.567 --> 46:59.800
Quick, get help!

46:59.800 --> 47:01.900
[ Groaning ]

47:03.333 --> 47:06.767
You gonna rip up me dad's debt
like you promised?

47:06.767 --> 47:09.067
You can tell Malky from me

47:09.067 --> 47:11.533
he's got an open line of credit
whenever he wants.

47:11.533 --> 47:13.067
[ Billy wailing ]

47:13.067 --> 47:15.267
You owe me, guard.

47:16.433 --> 47:18.167
Come on, Ron.

47:26.067 --> 47:27.800
[ Orla gasps ]

47:41.067 --> 47:42.200
[ No audio ]
